<Link id="l01387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1387"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1388"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: GetAbsDifference tries to compute the length of the function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1389"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// immediately, before the whole file is emitted, but in general</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1390"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that&#39;s impossible: the size in bytes of certain assembler directives</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1391"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// like .align and .fill is not known until the whole file is parsed and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1392"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// relaxations are applied. Currently, GetAbsDifference fails with a fatal</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1393"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// error in that case. (We mostly don&#39;t hit this because inline assembly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1394"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// specifying those directives is rare, and we don&#39;t normally try to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1395"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// align loops on AArch64.)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1396"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1397"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// There are two potential approaches to delaying the computation. One,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1398"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we could emit something like &quot;.word (endfunc-beginfunc)/4+0x10800000&quot;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1399"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// as long as we have some conservative estimate we could use to prove</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1400"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that we don&#39;t need to split the unwind data. Emitting the constant</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1401"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is straightforward, but there&#39;s no existing code for estimating the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1402"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// size of the function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1403"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1404"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The other approach would be to use a dedicated, relaxable fragment,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1405"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// which could grow to accommodate splitting the unwind data if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1406"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// necessary. This is more straightforward, since it automatically works</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1407"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// without any new infrastructure, and it&#39;s consistent with how we handle</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1408"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// relaxation in other contexts.  But it would require some refactoring</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1409"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to move parts of the pdata/xdata emission into the implementation of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1410"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a fragment. We could probably continue to encode the unwind codes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1411"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// here, but we&#39;d have to emit the pdata, the xdata header, and the</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1413"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// split the unwind data.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1414"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1415"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If this is fixed, remove code in AArch64ISelLowering.cpp that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1416"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// disables loop alignment on Windows.</span></CodeLine>
